<subSubSection id="C36E16BCDD7F03103F0EFF0FAF25FD5F" pageId="1" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BCB4537DD7F03103F0EFF0FAE99FE99" blockId="1.[282,1049,337,380]" pageId="1">
<heading id="D083F25BDD7F03103F0EFF0FAE99FE99" centered="true" fontSize="8" level="2" pageId="1" reason="2">
<emphasis id="B9009925DD7F03103F0EFF0FAE99FE99" bold="true" pageId="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103F0EFF0FAF7BFE81" authority="LeConte" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1847" box="[282,628,337,356]" class="Insecta" family="Brachyceridae" genus="Notiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novemstriatus">
<emphasis id="B9009925DD7F03103F0EFF0FAF17FE81" bold="true" box="[282,536,337,356]" italics="true" pageId="1">Notiophilus novemstriatus</emphasis>
LeConte
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103C96FF0FAFFBFE81" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[642,756,337,356]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103D14FF0FAE64FE81" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[768,875,337,356]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carabidae</taxonomicName>
), A New Ground Beetle for 
<collectingCountry id="F36305A7DD7F03103C13FF37AF5BFE99" box="[519,596,361,380]" name="Canada" pageId="1">Canada</collectingCountry>
from a Most Unlikely Location
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB4537DD7F03103F04FFC1AF25FD5F" blockId="1.[249,1083,415,1586]" pageId="1">
One specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103FA9FFC1AE02FE57" authority="LeConte" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1847" box="[445,781,415,434]" class="Insecta" family="Brachyceridae" genus="Notiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novemstriatus">
<emphasis id="B9009925DD7F03103FA9FFC1AFBBFE57" box="[445,692,415,434]" italics="true" pageId="1">Notiophilus novemstriatus</emphasis>
LeConte
</taxonomicName>
was obtained 
<date id="FFCA63F7DD7F03103D88FFC1A911FE57" box="[924,1054,415,434]" pageId="1" value="1996-05-22">
22 May 
<quantity id="4C8CE8D2DD7F03103DE4FFC1A911FE57" box="[1008,1054,415,434]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.06984" pageId="1" unit="in" value="1996.0">1996</quantity>
</date>
in open areas surrounding the southwest end of the Sydney Tar Ponds, Cape Breton County, Nova Scotia. This species has a wide distribution, in the 
<collectingCountry id="F36305A7DD7F03103D35FF91AEACFE07" box="[801,931,463,482]" name="United States of America" pageId="1">United States</collectingCountry>
, from 
<collectingRegion id="49B08BD5DD7F03103DF0FF91A910FE07" box="[996,1055,463,482]" country="United States of America" name="Maine" pageId="1">Maine</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="49B08BD5DD7F03103EEDFFB9AC33FE1F" box="[249,316,487,506]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="1">Florida</collectingRegion>
and west to 
<collectingRegion id="49B08BD5DD7F03103FAAFFB9AF06FE1F" box="[446,521,487,506]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="1">Arizona</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49B08BD5DD7F03103C28FFB9AF81FE1F" box="[572,654,487,506]" country="United States of America" name="Montana" pageId="1">Montana</collectingRegion>
(Lindroth, C. H. 1961. The Ground Beetles (
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103EEBFFA1AC6EFDF7" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[255,353,511,530]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carabidae</taxonomicName>
, excl. Cincindelinae) of 
<collectingCountry id="F36305A7DD7F03103C59FFA1AF9CFDF7" box="[589,659,511,530]" name="Canada" pageId="1">Canada</collectingCountry>
and Alaska Part II. Opuscula Entomologica Supplementum 20:1–200; Bousquet, Y. and Larochelle, A. 1993. Catalogue of the Geadephaga (
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103F41FC71ACCFFDA7" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[341,448,559,578]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103FD8FC71AF6EFDA7" authorityName="C.G. Thomson" authorityYear="1857" box="[460,609,559,578]" class="Insecta" family="Trachypachidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trachypachidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103C79FC71AFD2FDA7" authorityName="Laporte de Castelnau" authorityYear="1840" box="[621,733,559,578]" class="Insecta" family="Rhysodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Rhysodidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103CFCFC71AE49FDA7" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[744,838,559,578]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carabidae</taxonomicName>
including 
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103DBBFC71A917FDA7" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[943,1048,559,578]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cicindelini">Cicindelini</taxonomicName>
) of America North of Mexico. Memoirs of the Entomological Society of 
<collectingCountry id="F36305A7DD7F03103DBDFC19AEE0FDBF" box="[937,1007,583,602]" name="Canada" pageId="1">Canada</collectingCountry>
167:1– 397). Lindroth (1961:101) predicted that it would ‘possibly be discovered in Canada’, although up until now there have been no reports (Bousquet, Y. (ed.) 1991. Checklist of Beetles of 
<collectingCountry id="F36305A7DD7F03103F4AFCD1ACABFD47" box="[350,420,655,674]" name="Canada" pageId="1">Canada</collectingCountry>
and Alaska. Agriculture 
<collectingCountry id="F36305A7DD7F03103C86FCD1AFD7FD47" box="[658,728,655,674]" name="Canada" pageId="1">Canada</collectingCountry>
Publication 1861/E, Ottawa. 430 pp.; Bousquet and Larochelle 1993).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36E16BCDD7F03133F04FCE1AFF2FC2D" lastPageId="2" pageId="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCB4537DD7F03103F04FCE1A905FBB7" blockId="1.[249,1083,415,1586]" pageId="1">
<materialsCitation id="3B1C4F6ADD7F03103F04FCE1A909FBB7" collectionCode="V, SYSCO" collectorName="Lafontaine, J. D. &amp; Allyson, S. &amp; Borkent, A &amp; Campbell, J. M. &amp; Hamilton, K. G. A. &amp; Martin, J. E. H. &amp; Masner, L." country="Canada" county="Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park." location="The" municipality="Behan-Pelletier" pageId="1" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Nova Scotia">
<location id="8EAB13ECDD7F03103F04FCE1AC3BFD37" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DDF421DD7F03133F0EFF0FAFF2FC2D:8EAB13ECDD7F03103F04FCE1AC3BFD37" box="[272,308,703,722]" country="Canada" county="Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park." municipality="Behan-Pelletier" name="The" pageId="1" stateProvince="Nova Scotia">The</location>
ground beetle fauna of 
<location id="8EAB13ECDD7F03103C3CFCE1AFAEFD37" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DDF421DD7F03133F0EFF0FAFF2FC2D:8EAB13ECDD7F03103C3CFCE1AFAEFD37" box="[552,673,703,722]" country="Canada" county="Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park." municipality="Behan-Pelletier" name="Cape Breton" pageId="1" stateProvince="Nova Scotia">Cape Breton</location>
is reasonably well known, as a result of 
<location id="8EAB13ECDD7F03103EEDFC89AC48FD0F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DDF421DD7F03133F0EFF0FAFF2FC2D:8EAB13ECDD7F03103EEDFC89AC48FD0F" box="[249,327,727,746]" country="Canada" county="Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park." municipality="Behan-Pelletier" name="Brown's" pageId="1" stateProvince="Nova Scotia">Brown’s</location>
(
<emphasis id="B9009925DD7F03103F41FC89AC72FD0F" box="[341,381,727,746]" italics="true" pageId="1">e.g.,</emphasis>
1967. 
<location id="8EAB13ECDD7F03103FA9FC89ACFCFD0F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DDF421DD7F03133F0EFF0FAFF2FC2D:8EAB13ECDD7F03103FA9FC89ACFCFD0F" box="[445,499,727,746]" country="Canada" county="Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park." municipality="Behan-Pelletier" name="Notes" pageId="1" stateProvince="Nova Scotia">Notes</location>
on the extralimital distribution of some species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103DDAFC89A938FD0F" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[974,1079,727,746]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
. 
<location id="8EAB13ECDD7F03103EEDFCB1ACD9FCE7" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DDF421DD7F03133F0EFF0FAFF2FC2D:8EAB13ECDD7F03103EEDFCB1ACD9FCE7" box="[249,470,751,770]" country="Canada" county="Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park." municipality="Behan-Pelletier" name="Canadian Entomologist" pageId="1" stateProvince="Nova Scotia">Canadian Entomologist</location>
99:85–93.) work on introduced beetles, collecting trips by 
<location id="8EAB13ECDD7F03103A05FCB1AC25FCFF" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DDF421DD7F03133F0EFF0FAFF2FC2D:8EAB13ECDD7F03103A05FCB1AC25FCFF" country="Canada" county="Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park." municipality="Behan-Pelletier" name="Lindroth" pageId="1" stateProvince="Nova Scotia">Lindroth</location>
in the 1950’s and 1960’s (
<emphasis id="B9009925DD7F03103C3EFD59AF5DFCFF" box="[554,594,775,794]" italics="true" pageId="1">e.g.,</emphasis>
1954. 
<location id="8EAB13ECDD7F03103C80FD59AFD2FCFF" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DDF421DD7F03133F0EFF0FAFF2FC2D:8EAB13ECDD7F03103C80FD59AFD2FCFF" box="[660,733,775,794]" country="Canada" county="Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park." municipality="Behan-Pelletier" name="Carabid" pageId="1" stateProvince="Nova Scotia">Carabid</location>
beetles from 
<collectingRegion id="49B08BD5DD7F03103D75FD59AED7FCFF" box="[865,984,775,794]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="1">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
. 
<location id="8EAB13ECDD7F03103DF6FD59AC79FCD7" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DDF421DD7F03133F0EFF0FAFF2FC2D:8EAB13ECDD7F03103DF6FD59AC79FCD7" country="Canada" county="Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park." municipality="Behan-Pelletier" name="Canadian Entomologist" pageId="1" stateProvince="Nova Scotia">Canadian Entomologist</location>
86:299–310.) and a more recent survey by 
<location id="8EAB13ECDD7F03103D3EFD41AE9AFCD7" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DDF421DD7F03133F0EFF0FAFF2FC2D:8EAB13ECDD7F03103D3EFD41AE9AFCD7" box="[810,917,799,818]" country="Canada" county="Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park." municipality="Behan-Pelletier" name="Agriculture" pageId="1" stateProvince="Nova Scotia">Agriculture</location>
<collectingCountry id="F36305A7DD7F03103D8AFD41AEEBFCD7" box="[926,996,799,818]" name="Canada" pageId="1">Canada</collectingCountry>
of 
<location id="8EAB13ECDD7F03103A1EFD41AF27FCAF" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DDF421DD7F03133F0EFF0FAFF2FC2D:8EAB13ECDD7F03103A1EFD41AF27FCAF" country="Canada" county="Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park." municipality="Behan-Pelletier" name="Cape Breton Highlands National Park" pageId="1" stateProvince="Nova Scotia">Cape Breton Highlands National Park</location>
(
<collectorName id="268120E1DD7F03103C21FD69AFD9FCAF" box="[565,726,823,842]" pageId="1">Lafontaine, J. D.</collectorName>
, 
<collectorName id="268120E1DD7F03103CF5FD69AE44FCAF" box="[737,843,823,842]" pageId="1">Allyson, S.</collectorName>
, 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BAFDF4DDD7F03103D42FD69AEE8FCAF" box="[854,999,823,842]" pageId="1">Behan­Pelletier</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED65DDF2DD7F03103DE4FD69A90CFCAF" box="[1008,1027,823,842]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="1" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
., 
<collectorName id="268120E1DD7F03103A04FD69AC4CFC87" pageId="1">Borkent, A</collectorName>
. 
<collectorName id="268120E1DD7F03103F5BFD11ACE2FC87" box="[335,493,847,866]" pageId="1">Campbell, J. M.</collectorName>
, 
<collectorName id="268120E1DD7F03103FEDFD11AFB8FC87" box="[505,695,847,866]" pageId="1">Hamilton, K. G. A.</collectorName>
, 
<collectorName id="268120E1DD7F03103CD0FD11AE50FC87" box="[708,863,847,866]" pageId="1">Martin, J. E. H.</collectorName>
, and 
<collectorName id="268120E1DD7F03103D82FD11AEF2FC87" box="[918,1021,847,866]" pageId="1">Masner, L.</collectorName>
1987. The Insects, Spiders and 
<collectingCounty id="62AA3DBBDD7F03103FF3FD39AEA7FC9F" box="[487,936,871,890]" pageId="1">Mites of Cape Breton Highlands National Park.</collectingCounty>
Biosystematics Research Centre, Agriculture 
<collectingCountry id="F36305A7DD7F03103C1AFD21AF59FC77" box="[526,598,895,914]" name="Canada" pageId="1">Canada</collectingCountry>
, Ottawa. 302 pp.). In 1995 my students and I started collecting in open areas surrounding the Sydney Tar Ponds. The Tar Ponds are the remnants of a larger water body, shrunk by urban development. They are infamous because of their role as repositories for decades of industrial waste from 
<collectionCode id="ED65DDF2DD7F03103D88FD99AEE8FC3F" box="[924,999,967,986]" pageId="1">SYSCO</collectionCode>
(Sydney Steel Company and its predecessors), the associated coke ovens and domestic sewage. The goal was to compare the community of introduced beetles in an anthropogenic habitat with that found by Brown more than 30 years earlier. During the summer of 1995 we collected using 
<collectingMethod id="52353D20DD7F03103FACFA79ACF4FBDF" box="[440,507,1063,1082]" pageId="1">pitfalls</collectingMethod>
, 
<collectingMethod id="52353D20DD7F03103C1CFA79AFA5FBDF" box="[520,682,1063,1082]" pageId="1">yellow pan traps</collectingMethod>
and by hand throughout the summer. In 1996 efforts were focused in May and June, with an emphasis on hand collecting
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB4537DD7F03103F04FA09A934FA97" blockId="1.[249,1083,415,1586]" pageId="1">
On 
<date id="FFCA63F7DD7F03103F23FA09ACB4FB8F" box="[311,443,1111,1130]" pageId="1" value="1996-05-22">22 May 1996</date>
four people collected beetles by hand, searching under logs and rocks on the south west corner, especially between the railway lines and the ponds and in debris among the few cattails on the opposite shore. During this effort one 
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103DD9FAD9AC74FB57" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1847" class="Insecta" family="Brachyceridae" genus="Notiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novemstriatus">
<emphasis id="B9009925DD7F03103DD9FAD9AC74FB57" italics="true" pageId="1">Notiophilus novemstriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected. Danny Shpeley, University of 
<collectingRegion id="49B08BD5DD7F03103D27FAC1AE74FB57" box="[819,891,1183,1202]" country="Canada" name="Alberta" pageId="1">Alberta</collectingRegion>
, identified the specimen and when it was deposited in the Canadian National Insect Collection, Agriculture 
<collectingCountry id="F36305A7DD7F03103EEDFA91AC4EFB07" box="[249,321,1231,1250]" name="Canada" pageId="1">Canada</collectingCountry>
, Ottawa, Yves Bousquet corroborated the identification. Other carabids collected that day included 
<taxonomicName id="4C743EB4DD7F03103FB6FAB9AFBDFB1F" authority="Casey" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1924" box="[418,690,1255,1274]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canadensis">
<emphasis id="B9009925DD7F03103FB6FAB9AF7EFB1F" box="[418,625,1255,1274]" italics="true" pageId="1">Acupalpus canadensis</emphasis>
Casey
</taxonomicName>
, 
